The textured LaTeX document class and supporting files
======================================================

Copyright 2024-2026 Jonas Dujava

This work may be distributed and/or modified under the conditions of
the LaTeX Project Public License, either version 1.3c of this license
or (at your option) any later version.

The latest version of this license is in
  https://www.latex-project.org/lppl.txt
and version 1.3c or later is part of all distributions of LaTeX
version 2008-05-04 or later.

This work has the LPPL maintenance status `maintained'.

The Current Maintainer of this work is Jonas Dujava.

This work consists of the files:
  textured.cls
  textured-debug.sty
  textured-envs.sty
  textured-general.sty
  textured-hacks.sty
  textured-layout.sty
  textured-math.sty
  textured-misc.sty
  textured-biblatex.sty
  glyphtounicode.tex
  textured.bib

the frontmatter template files:
  frontmatter/title.tex
  frontmatter/declaration.tex
  frontmatter/dedication.tex
  frontmatter/information.tex
  frontmatter/README.md

and the documentation files:
  README.md
  CHANGELOG.md
  thesis.pdf (generated from the manual source)

---

Note: Example files provided in the examples/ directory are
provided as-is for demonstration purposes and may be freely
used, modified, and distributed without restriction.

---

MFF CUNI Logo Attribution
==========================

The MFF CUNI logo (frontmatter/img/MFF-logo.pdf) is property of the
Faculty of Mathematics and Physics, Charles University, Prague.

The logo is included with the class for convenience when creating
theses for MFF CUNI, but remains the intellectual property of the
university. For official usage guidelines, see:
  https://www.mff.cuni.cz/en/faculty/visual-identity
